message.content:
A Turdus fuscater is a bird species found in South America.
It has a dark brown plumage on its back and wings.
Its underparts are a lighter brown color with dark spots.
The feathers on its head are darker than the rest of its body.
It has a grayish-white eye ring and a yellowish beak.
The Turdus fuscater is often found in forested areas or near bodies of water.
It feeds on fruit and insects.
